  "prompt": "How long will a Google shortened URL be available?",
  "response": "Google's URL shortener, **goo.gl**, was officially discontinued by Google in **April 2019**. However, any URLs that were created before the shutdown will **continue to work indefinitely**, as long as the destination links are valid and no one removes them.\n\nThat said, Google no longer provides support or a dashboard for managing or tracking these shortened URLs. If you need to create or manage shortened URLs today, Google recommends using alternative services like **Bitly**, **TinyURL**, or **Firebase Dynamic Links**.\n\nIf you have an existing goo.gl shortened URL, it will remain active unless:\n1. The destination link becomes broken or invalid.\n2. The shortened URL is manually deleted by the owner.\n3. Google decides to remove the service entirely in the future.\n\nTo ensure long-term reliability, consider replacing goo.gl links with a more current URL shortening service.",
